    "body": "## Problem\r\nfolding range/code lens maintenance involves many tables with a size equal to the number of buffer lines. Although these tables should share the same lifecycle as the buffer, they are often cleared using `t = {}` when new data arrives. This increases the GC burden and causes the next data insertion to trigger a rehash and memory reallocation.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nUsing LuaJIT's `require('table.clear')` allows for efficient table clearing, avoiding unnecessary GC and memory reallocation. This PR adds a new shim to provide support for PUC Lua.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
